Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` must not be null.
- The length of the input array `nums` must be greater than or equal to `k`.
- The value of `k` must be between 1 and the length of the input array `nums`, inclusive.
- The input array `nums` must contain integers.

Postconditions:
- The method should return an integer, which is the `k`th largest element in the input array `nums`.
- The returned integer should be one of the elements in the input array `nums`.
- The returned integer should be the `k`th largest element in the sorted order of the input array `nums`.